        "body": "Yeah, I think we could probably take this on.  Let's use this thread to iterate on design / get broad agreement.  Right now the proposal is just search locally -- do you think we'd want some mechanism for the user to ask where the configuration is being loaded from ?  For example, conda can do this in the following way:\r\n\r\n```\r\n(base) bzaitlen@dgx15:~$ conda config --show-sources\r\n==> /home/nfs/bzaitlen/.condarc <==\r\nchannels:\r\n  - conda-forge\r\n  - defaults\r\nreport_errors: False\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe also explored providing this feedback in dask-cuda with https://github.com/rapidsai/dask-cuda/pull/1006 (though the name is not great and may also change) and asked about it here: https://github.com/dask/distributed/issues/7106\r\n\r\nMy guess is this shouldn't be too hard to implement but we should just check with others like @jacobtomlinson / @jrbourbeau to make sure this isn't too \"magical\" ",
