        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Apologies for the delayed reply. My initial reaction was \"our config system already has lots of places it looks, do we really need another?\" But after thinking about it more, I'm +0.5 for adding support for a config file in the current working directly. \r\n\r\nThings I don't like about it:\r\n\r\n- It's yet another place where config files could be\r\n\r\nThings I do like about it:\r\n\r\n- Makes it easier to include/use a Dask config file in a project (e.g. `git add .dask.yaml` + `git commit -m \"Adds custom Dask config\"`)\r\n    - @quasiben mentioned offline that he's run into multiple user groups who wanted an easy way to have a different config file per project. The change proposed here would resolve that user pain. \r\n- Easier to remember for Dask devs who want to experiment locally (this is @gjoseph92 wants) \r\n- This change is backwards compatible.\r\n\r\nAlso cc @djhoese for visibility ",
